Raj Koothrappali Was Dave Koothrappali
text:
There is a link to the pitch of Star Trek posted on HN. I browsed through that website[0] to see what else I could find. And I saw lots of script for other tele series since 2006!

Intrigued, I started looking for anything by Chuck Lorre and Bill Prady (more specifically "The Big Bang Theory"). And I found the script of the pilot for The Big Bang Theory. In that script[1] the name of Raj Koothrappali is Dave Koothrappali :)

0. https://sites.google.com/site/tvwriting

1. https://www.zen134237.zen.co.uk/Big_Bang_Theory/The_Big_Bang_Theory_1x01_-_Pilot.pdf

Ask HN: Which of the yesterday's hardware are you tinkering with?
text:
I see lots of people enjoy collecting and tinkering with old computers.

What's your favorite, if any? Apple II, C64, ZX Spectrum, PC, Commodore Amiga, Atari ST, Sun Sparc, PowerPC, random Motorola 68, SGI?

I love all but since I have limited space in my home I am mostly interested in C64, Amiga and Atari.
